      <abstract id="aspace_415cb4c6d80c87136744b62f119fc0e7">A collection of typewritten copies of letters written by Daniel I. Underhill, a Civil War soldier, to his family on Long Island. The letters are dated 1862 to 1863. Original copies of the letters were owned by R.J. Cooke of Oceanside, NY, who donated the typewritten copies to the Long Island Historical Society (later known as the Brooklyn Historical Society).</abstract>
